    <oio:id>nuclex:000491</oio:id>
    <nuclex:definition>A radiopharmaceutical designed to be administered to a patient to deliver ionizing radiation directly to targeted tissues or cells for the purpose of treating diseases, primarily cancer. They typically use beta or alpha particle emissions to induce cellular damage within the targeted tissues.</nuclex:definition>
